After the conclusion of today’s trial hearing, the Trial Chamber of the Extraordinary Chambers in the Courts of Cambodia (ECCC) adjourned for a judicial recess in Case 002 until 16 July 2012. 
The next trial hearing will commence at 9 am on Monday 16 July, when the Trial Chamber is expected to start hearing testimony from Dr. David Chandler.
Since the commencement of the opening statements in Case 002 on 21 November 2011, the Trial Chamber has concluded 78 trial days. 
A total of 18 witnesses, experts and Civil Parties have appeared before the Trial Chamber. 
As of 21 June 2012, a total of 43,626 persons have attended the trial hearings in Case 002.
Complete list of witnesses, experts and Civil Parties  who have appeared before the Trial Chamber:http://www.eccc.gov.kh/en/case/topic/2?quicktabs_1=4#quicktabs-1